ingradients: 1 pound beef sirloin, cut into thin strips
cooking_methods: In a large skillet, heat the vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the beef and cook until browned on all sides. Remove beef from skillet and set aside.Add the onion, garlic, and mushrooms to the skillet and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.Remove the vegetables from the skillet and set aside with the beef.In the same skillet, melt the butter over medium heat. Whisk in the flour and cook for 1-2 minutes, stirring constantly.Gradually whisk in the beef broth until the mixture is smooth. Stir in the Dijon mustard.Add the beef and vegetables back to the skillet and let the mixture simmer for 10-15 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened.Remove the skillet from heat and stir in the sour cream. Season with salt and pepper to taste.Serve the stroganoff over cooked egg noodles, garnished with chopped parsley. Enjoy!
